ğŸ”¹ 1. index.php (Main Form Page)
<?php session_start(); ?>
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>User Form</title>
</head>
<body>

<h2>Enter Details</h2>

<form action="process.php" method="POST">
    Username: <input type="text" name="username" required><br><br>
    Phone Number: <input type="text" name="phone_number" required><br><br>
    <button type="submit">Submit</button>
</form>

</body>
</html>

ğŸ”¹ 2. process.php (Convert Names Here ğŸ”¥)
<?php
session_start();

// Getting original fields
$username = $_POST['username'];
$phone    = $_POST['phone_number'];

// Converting field names
$_SESSION['name']   = $username;   // username â†’ name
$_SESSION['mobile'] = $phone;      // phone_number â†’ mobile

header("Location: home.php");
exit();
?>

ğŸ”¹ 3. home.php (Reflected Here)
<?php
session_start();
if (!isset($_SESSION['name'])) {
    header("Location: index.php");
    exit();
}
?>

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Home</title>
</head>
<body>

<h2>Home Page</h2>

Name: <?php echo $_SESSION['name']; ?><br>
Mobile: <?php echo $_SESSION['mobile']; ?><br><br>

<a href="profile.php">Go to Profile</a><br>
<a href="logout.php">Logout</a>

</body>
</html>

ğŸ”¹ 4. profile.php (Also Reflected Automatically)
<?php
session_start();
if (!isset($_SESSION['name'])) {
    header("Location: index.php");
    exit();
}
?>

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Profile</title>
</head>
<body>

<h2>Profile Page</h2>

Welcome, <?php echo $_SESSION['name']; ?>!<br>
Your Mobile Number is <?php echo $_SESSION['mobile']; ?><br><br>

<a href="home.php">Back to Home</a>

</body>
</html>

ğŸ”¹ 5. logout.php
<?php
session_start();
session_destroy();
header("Location: index.php");
exit();
?>

ğŸ¯ How This Works
Original Field	Converted Field	Used Everywhere
username	name	$_SESSION['name']
phone_number	mobile	$_SESSION['mobile']

So if tomorrow you change:

$_SESSION['full_name']
$_SESSION['contact_no']


Only process.php needs update â€” all pages reflect ğŸ’¥

ğŸ§  Interview One-Line Answer

We store form data in session variables with standardized names, so changes in field naming reflect across all pages without modifying each file.
